    "Access to dermatologists is a problem, especially in rural areas, where it may take longer for a patient to obtain a biopsy of suspected melanoma (94).",
    "As of 2018, 69% of counties in the United States do not have access to dermatologists (95).",
    "Further exacerbating the issue, many dermatology clinics closed during the COVID-19 pandemic (96).",
    "AI-augmented teledermatology may be able to enhance accessibility by streamlining referrals and reducing waiting times, and it could help increase the accessibility in areas with a scarcity of dermatopathologists.",
    "AI may also help dermatologists more accurately diagnose skin disease in patients whose skin is not well-represented in the local population (97)."
  ],
